#: ../../firewall.rst:11
msgid ""
"Firewall rules define how network traffic is segmented and controlled "
"between different zones. Firewalls acts as barriers between trusted "
"internal networks and untrusted external networks, such as the internet. "
"These rules specify which traffic is allowed, denied, or monitored based "
"on predefined security policies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall.rst:15
msgid ""
"The order of rules is important; the first matching rule is applied, "
"determining the fate of the network packet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall.rst:17
msgid ""
