"future reference and management. By providing a descriptive and "
"meaningful name, network administrators can easily identify the purpose "
"and context of each port forward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../port_forward.rst:20
msgid "``Source port``: the port from which the request originates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../port_forward.rst:21
msgid ""
"``Destination port``: the port to which the traffic is directed; this can"
" differ from the source port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../port_forward.rst:22
msgid ""
"``Protocol``: specifies the protocol such as ``TCP``, ``UDP``, "
"``UDPLITE``, ``ICMP``, ``ESP``, ``AH`` ``SCTP`` or the special value "
"``ALL`` for all supported protocols."
